PARITY-ODD POWER SPECTRA (TB, EB) IN RCG + CHIRAL GRAVITY
=========================================================
See: CHIRAL ISW CONTRIBUTION https://github.com/JDRedding/RCG-Relational-Cosmological-Geometry/blob/main/CHIRAL%20ISW%20CONTRIBUTION

Temperature multipoles:
    a_{ℓm}^T =
        a_{ℓm}^{T,iso}
      + a_{ℓm}^{T,Q}
      + a_{ℓm}^{T,D}
      + a_{ℓm}^{T,Π}

Chiral temperature piece:
    a_{ℓm}^{T,Π} ∝ γ_Π ⟨ Y_{ℓm}, Π M_{2,3} ⟩

Polarization multipoles:
    a_{ℓm}^E, a_{ℓm}^B

Chiral B-mode sourcing:
    a_{ℓm}^{B,Π} ∝ ε_Π ⟨ {}_2Y_{ℓm}, Π M_{2,3} ⟩

    where:
        ε_Π = strength of chiral coupling into B-modes

Parity-odd spectra:

    C_ℓ^{TB} =
        (1 / (2ℓ + 1)) Σ_m
            Re[ a_{ℓm}^{T,Π} (a_{ℓm}^{B,Π})* ]

    C_ℓ^{EB} =
        (1 / (2ℓ + 1)) Σ_m
            Re[ a_{ℓm}^{E,Π} (a_{ℓm}^{B,Π})* ]

Structurally:
    C_ℓ^{TB}, C_ℓ^{EB} ∼
        f_ℓ( A_Q, A_D, γ_Π, ε_Π ; Π M_{2,3}, d^ )

    i.e. they are determined by:
        • low-ℓ anomaly amplitudes A_Q, A_D
        • chiral ISW amplitude γ_Π
        • chiral polarization coupling ε_Π
        • geometry of Π M_{2,3} and preferred direction d^

LOW-ℓ SCALING OF PARITY-ODD SPECTRA (TB, EB) IN RCG + CHIRAL GRAVITY
